* {{ill|Kami-Ishizu Misanzai Kofun|ja|上石津ミサンザイ古墳|1=Kami-Ishizu Misanzai Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Sakai|ja|堺市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Richū" (Mozu Miminashi no Mihara no Minami no Misasagi). On Sakai City's website,<ref>[http://www.city.sakai.lg.jp/kanko/rekishi/dkofun/database/richutenno.html Mausoleum of Emperor Richū (Misanzai Kofun, Ishizugaoka Kofun, Mozu Ryōzan Kofun)] (Sakai City website, updated December 19, 2012).</ref> it is also simply referred to as Misanzai Kofun. * {{ill|Haji Nisanzai Kofun|ja|土師ニサンザイ古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} (Sakai, Osaka Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Eastern Mozu {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|12=draft|12=draft}}." * {{ill|Okamisanzai Kofun|ja|岡ミサンザイ古墳|1=Okamisanzai Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Fujiidera|ja|藤井寺市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Osaka Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Chūai" (Ega Nagano no Nishi no Misasagi). * {{ill|Tannowa Nisanzai Kofun|ja|淡輪ニサンザイ古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Misaki|ja|岬町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sennan District|ja|泉南郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, Osaka Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Grave of Itsu-nii-shikiiri-hiko-no-Mikoto" (Udo no Haka). * Nishinisanzai Kofun (西ニサンザイ古墳 or 西二山在古墳) (Misaki, Sennan District, Osaka Prefecture) - Another name for the {{ill|Seiryō Kofun|ja|西陵古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, a nationally designated Historic Site. * {{ill|Toriya Misanzai Kofun|ja|鳥屋ミサンザイ古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} (alternatively called "Toriya Misanzai Kofun" or "Toriya Misanzai Kofun") ({{ill|Kashihara|ja|橿原市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Senka" (Misasagi Momoka Torisakaue no Misasagi). * Shijō Misanzai (四条ミサンザイ) (Kashihara, Nara Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Jimmu" (Unebi Yamato Hokuryō). It is unclear whether this site is a kofun. See also {{ill|Shijō Kofun Group|ja|四条古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}}.
