ct, Osaka Prefecture) - Another name for the {{ill|Seiryō Kofun|ja|西陵古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seiryō Kofun|qq=}}, a nationally designated Historic Site. * {{ill|Toriya Misanzai Kofun|ja|鳥屋ミサンザイ古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toriya Misanzai Kofun|qq=}} (alternatively called "Toriya Misanzai Kofun" or "Toriya Misanzai Kofun") ({{ill|Kashihara|ja|橿原市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashihara|qq=}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nara Prefecture|qq=}}) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Senka" (Misasagi Momoka Torisakaue no Misasagi). * Shijō Misanzai (四条ミサンザイ) (Kashihara, Nara Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Jimmu" (Unebi Yamato Hokuryō). It is unclear whether this site is a kofun. See also {{ill|Shijō Kofun Group|ja|四条古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shijō Kofun Group|qq=}}.
