* {{ill|Kami-Ishizu Misanzai Kofun|ja|上石津ミサンザイ古墳|1=Kami-Ishizu Misanzai Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami-Ishizu Misanzai Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami-Ishizu Misanzai Kofun|qq=}} ([[:en:Sakai|Sakai]], [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]]) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Richū" (Mozu Miminashi no Mihara no Minami no Misasagi). On Sakai City's website,<ref>[http://www.city.sakai.lg.jp/kanko/rekishi/dkofun/database/richutenno.html Mausoleum of Emperor Richū (Misanzai Kofun, Ishizugaoka Kofun, Mozu Ryōzan Kofun)] (Sakai City website, updated December 19, 2012).</ref> it is also simply referred to as Misanzai Kofun. * {{ill|Haji Nisanzai Kofun|ja|土師ニサンザイ古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haji Nisanzai Kofun|qq=}} (Sakai, Osaka Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Eastern Mozu {{ill|Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|13=User:Immanuelle/Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|qq=}}." * {{ill|Okamisanzai Kofun|ja|岡ミサンザイ古墳|1=Okamisanzai Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okamisanzai Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Okamisanzai Kofun|qq=}} ([[:en:Fujiidera|Fujiidera]], Osaka Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Chūai" (Ega Nagano no Nishi no Misasagi). * {{ill|Tannowa Nisanzai Kofun|ja|淡輪ニサンザイ古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tannowa Nisanzai Kofun|qq=}} ([[:en:Misaki, Osaka|Misaki]], [[:en:Sennan District, Osaka|Sennan District]], Osaka Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Grave of Itsu-nii-shikiiri-hiko-no-Mikoto" (Udo no Haka). * Nishinisanzai Kofun (西ニサンザイ古墳 or 西二山在古墳) (Misaki, Sennan District, Osaka Prefecture) - Another name for the [[:en:Sairyō Kofun|Seiryō Kofun]], a nationally designated Historic Site. * {{ill|Toriya Misanzai Kofun|ja|鳥屋ミサンザイ古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toriya Misanzai Kofun|qq=}} (alternatively called "Toriya Misanzai Kofun" or "Toriya Misanzai Kofun") ([[:en:Kashihara, Nara|Kashihara]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]]) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Senka" (Misasagi Momoka Torisakaue no Misasagi). * Shijō Misanzai (四条ミサンザイ) (Kashihara, Nara Prefecture) - Designated by the Imperial Household Agency as the "Mausoleum of Emperor Jimmu" (Unebi Yamato Hokuryō). It is unclear whether this site is a kofun. See also {{ill|Shijō Kofun Group|ja|四条古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shijō Kofun Group|qq=}}.
